sql:
SELECT DISTINCT m.title, d.name
FROM movies m
JOIN directors d ON m.director_id = d.id;

external_knowledge:
In this context, 'crown jewels of the cinema world' refers to the most highly rated and popular movies based on user reviews and ratings; 
A movie's popularity can be gauged by the number of users who rated it and the total number of reviews; 
The 'most popular' refers to the highest average rating, the most ratings, the most users who rated, and the most reviews.

sql:
SELECT AVG(r.rating) 
FROM movies m 
JOIN ratings r ON m.id = r.movie_id 
WHERE m.director_id = (
    SELECT id FROM directors WHERE name = 'Steven Spielberg'
);

